{
  "id": 36264,
  "kuerzel": "M_IPCV1",
  "bezeichnung": "Image Processing and Computer Vision 1",
  "kreditpunkte": 4,
  "lernziele": "<p>Image Processing and Computer Vision 1 and Image Processing and Computer Vision 2 form together a one-year introductory sequence into modern digital image processing and computer vision</p>",
  "vorausgKenntnisse": "<ul>\n<li>Fundamental knowledge of multivariable calculus</li>\n<li>Fundamental knowledge of Fourier analysis</li>\n<li>Fundamental knowledge of probability theory</li>\n<li>Fundamental knowledge of linear algebra</li>\n<li>Fundamental skills using Python as a programming language</li>\n<li>Solid command of the English language, since the lectures are in English</li>\n</ul>",
  "semesterBewertung": "keine Note oder Wertung",
  "sprache": "de-CH",
  "zustand": "aktiviert",
  "kurse": [
    {
      "id": 36263,
      "kuerzel": "IPCV1",
      "bezeichnung": "Image Processing and Computer Vision 1",
      "lernziele": "<p>At the end of the module the students are expected to understand the following concepts and be able to apply them to real world image processing and computer vision problems:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Digital Image Formation</li>\n<li>Geometric Transformations</li>\n<li>Image Segmentation</li>\n<li>Image Filtering in the spatial Domain</li>\n<li>Image Filtering in the frequency Domain</li>\n<li>Image Restoration</li>\n<li>Further Topics</li>\n</ul>",
      "planinhalt": "<p>The module is structured as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Digital Image Formation</li>\n<li>Geometric Transformations</li>\n<li>Image Segmentation</li>\n<li>Image Filtering in the spatial Domain</li>\n<li>Image Filtering in the frequency Domain</li>\n<li>Image Restoration</li>\n<li>Further Topics</li>\n</ul>",
      "bibliographie": "<p>The module is based on lecture slides, exercises and the book: \"Digital Image Processing, 4th ed.\" by Rafael C.Gonzalez and Richard E. Woods. There is a website dedicated to this book with useful information: http://www.imageprocessingplace.com/</p>",
